<br>
I used to smoke, I quit about 2 years ago and never looked back. Smoking was a nervous habit for me. If I needed a time-out or whatnot, a nice cigarette was a good reason to &quot;get-away.&quot;<br>
<br>
Then one day, I just got sick of my sinuses always being screwed-up, always hacking up a lung if I got remotely sick, consistently getting bronchitis, and always out of breath when it came to doing exercises or sports.<br>
<br>
So I quit mid-cigarette one afternoon at work, grinded the rest of the pack of smokes in the ground, and walked away.<br>
<br>
